    "On the other hand, Figure 8b shows that even for the sample with T span > 200 days, a large part of the data points is still located in the lower left region of the diagram.",
    "This fact suggests that for this portion of stellar sources, if there are long-term trends of Hα activity, the amplitude of the long-term variations must be lower.",
    "As for the stellar sources with higher activity intensity (log R median Hα > -4.85), there is no evidence of distinct distribution configurations between the long-term and short-term variations of Hα activity, as shown in Figures 8 and 9b.",
    "Meunier et al (2022) analyzed the long-term and short-term variability of stellar Hα and Ca II H and K activity by using the HARPS spectral data.",
    "Most of the stellar objects in their sample are old solar-type main-sequence stars."
